article.headline: Southern Miss 84, Tennessee State 74
article.story: HATTIESBURG, Miss. (AP) -- Jarekus Singleton had a season-high 21 points to lead Southern Mississippi past Tennessee State 84-74 on Monday night. Bruce Price had 27 points to lead Tennessee State (2-3), which led by as many as 14 before Southern Miss (4-6) rallied behind Jason Forte, who had 14 of his career-high 18 points in the second half. Southern Miss has won consecutive games for the first time in the past year. The Golden Eagles, who beat William Carey last week, are in the midst of their best run since winning six straight in December 2004. Tennessee State led 34-20 late in the first half before Southern Miss rallied to make it a 5-point game at halftime. The Golden Eagles then outscored the Tigers 50-35 in the second half for the victory. Courtney Beasley also had a career-high 18 points for Southern Miss. Mildon Ambres had 14 rebounds for the Golden Eagles. Kareem Grant added 18 points for Tennessee State and Clarence Matthews added 12.
